<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Aravindhan – Interview Reference Card</title>
<style>
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif; background: #0f1117; color: #e8e8e8; min-height: 100vh; padding: 16px; }
  h1 { text-align: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 4px; padding-top: 8px; }
  .subtitle { text-align: center; font-size: 13px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .tabs { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .tab { padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 20px; border: 1px solid #333; background: #1a1d27; color: #aaa; font-size: 13px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; }
  .tab.active { background: #2563eb; border-color: #2563eb; color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { display: none; }
  .section.active { display: block; }
  .card { background: #1a1d27; border: 1px solid #2a2d3a; border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .card-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #2563eb; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .question { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .answer { font-size: 14px; color: #ccc; line-height: 1.7; background: #0f1117; border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px; border-left: 3px solid #2563eb; position: relative; }
  .answer[contenteditable="true"] { outline: none; border-left-color: #f59e0b; }
  .edit-btn { position: absolute; top: 8px; right: 8px; background: #2a2d3a; border: none; color: #888; font-size: 11px; padding: 3px 8px; border-radius: 6px; cursor: pointer; }
  .edit-btn:hover { color: #fff; background: #3a3d4a; }
  .tip { font-size: 12px; color: #f59e0b; margin-top: 8px; padding: 6px 10px; background: #1f1a0a; border-radius: 6px; }
  .highlight { color: #34d399; font-weight: 600; }
  .ctc-input { background: #0f1117; border: 1px solid #2563eb; border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 10px; color: #fff; font-size: 14px; width: 120px; margin: 0 6px; }
  .ctc-input:focus { outline: none; border-color: #f59e0b; }
  .section-label { font-size: 11px; color: #666; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 8px; margin-top: 16px; }
  .checklist { list-style: none; }
  .checklist li { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px; padding: 8px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2d3a; font-size: 14px; color: #ccc; }
  .checklist li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .check { width: 18px; height: 18px; border-radius: 4px; border: 2px solid #2563eb; flex-shrink: 0; cursor: pointer; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; margin-top: 1px; }
  .check.done { background: #2563eb; border-color: #2563eb; }
  .check.done::after { content: '✓'; color: #fff; font-size: 11px; }
  .badge { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px; font-weight: 600; margin-left: 6px; }
  .badge-green { background: #052e16; color: #34d399; }
  .badge-yellow { background: #1c1202; color: #f59e0b; }
  .rules { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
  .rule { background: #0f1117; border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px; border-left: 3px solid #34d399; font-size: 14px; color: #ccc; }
  .rule strong { color: #fff; }
  #ctc-display { color: #34d399; font-weight: 600; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>🎯 Aravindhan – Interview Reference</h1>
<p class="subtitle">Open this before every call. Tap any answer to edit it.</p>

<div class="tabs">
  <div class="tab active" onclick="showTab('screening')">📞 Screening Call</div>
  <div class="tab" onclick="showTab('technical')">💻 Technical</div>
  <div class="tab" onclick="showTab('checklist')">✅ Checklist</div>
  <div class="tab" onclick="showTab('rules')">📋 Golden Rules</div>
</div>

<!-- SCREENING TAB -->
<div class="section active" id="screening">

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">💰 Your CTC (fill this once)</div>
    <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:8px; font-size:14px; color:#ccc;">
      My current CTC is
      <input class="ctc-input" id="ctc-val" type="text" placeholder="e.g. 9.5" oninput="updateCTC()"> LPA
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">👋 Tell me about yourself</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true" id="intro">I'm Aravindhan, currently working as a Technology Analyst at Infosys for the past 3 years. I specialise in Oracle PL/SQL development — building enterprise database applications, performance tuning, and production support. I've worked on large-scale logistics projects for global clients like Sysco and CMA CGM, handling everything from complex PL/SQL packages to critical P1/P2 production incidents. I'm now looking for a role where I can deepen my Oracle expertise and take on more challenging database problems.</div>
    <div class="tip">⏱ Keep it under 45 seconds. Don't ramble.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">🔄 Why are you looking to change?</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">I've had great exposure at Infosys — working on enterprise-scale Oracle applications for global clients. I'm now looking for a role with more technical depth and ownership, where I can work on more complex database challenges and grow into a senior Oracle developer.</div>
    <div class="tip">⚠️ Never say anything negative about Infosys.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">📅 About the gap (2018–2022)</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">After my engineering degree I spent time transitioning from mechanical to IT — self-learning Oracle databases and SQL development before joining Infosys in 2022.</div>
    <div class="tip">✅ One sentence. Confident. Move on immediately.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">🗓 Notice period</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">My current notice period is 90 days, but I can discuss early release depending on the opportunity.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">💵 Current & Expected CTC</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="false" id="ctc-answer">My current CTC is <span id="ctc-display">[fill CTC above]</span> LPA. Based on my skills and market research I'm looking at 16 to 20 LPA, but I'm open to discussion based on the role and growth opportunity.</div>
    <div class="tip">💡 Never give a single number. Always a range. Never apologise for your expectation.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">💪 What are your strengths?</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">My strongest area is Oracle PL/SQL — I've independently designed complex packages, optimised slow-running queries, and resolved critical production incidents under pressure. I'm also comfortable mentoring junior developers and leading code reviews.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">🏢 Are you interviewing elsewhere?</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">Yes I have a couple of conversations ongoing, but I'm genuinely interested in this role specifically.</div>
    <div class="tip">💡 Always say yes — it creates urgency.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">❓ Questions to ask them (end of call)</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">Can you tell me about the kind of Oracle applications the team works on and the scale of the database environment?</div>
    <div style="margin-top:10px;" class="answer" contenteditable="true">What are the next steps and the expected timeline?</div>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- TECHNICAL TAB -->
<div class="section" id="technical">

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">🔑 Key things to mention naturally</div>
    <ul style="list-style:none; display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:8px; margin-top:4px;">
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">Oracle 12c</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">PL/SQL Packages</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">Performance Tuning</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">AWR Reports</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">DBMS_STATS</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">Execution Plan</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">BULK COLLECT</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">P1/P2 Incidents</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">25+ Enhancements</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-green">15+ Releases</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-yellow">XML/JSON Integration</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-yellow">SQL Loader</span></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">⚡ Your strongest stories — use in technical rounds</div>

    <div class="section-label">Story 1 — Performance Tuning</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">I worked on a slow-running query that was causing P2 incidents in production. I used AWR reports and Execution Plan analysis to identify a full table scan on a large table. Added a composite index and rewrote the query using BULK COLLECT instead of row-by-row processing. This significantly reduced execution time and resolved the recurring incident.</div>

    <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:14px;">Story 2 — Complex Requirement</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">I led the resolution of a complex sublease invoice processing requirement — it involved large-volume data analysis, query optimisation, calculation corrections, and external system integration. I coordinated across multiple teams under a strict delivery timeline and delivered it successfully with zero defects.</div>

    <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:14px;">Story 3 — End to End Development</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">I designed and built an Oracle Forms module from scratch — it had 6 to 7 canvases, integrated with 5+ database tables, and had a backend PL/SQL package with 20+ procedures and functions. I handled everything from requirement analysis to deployment and post-release support.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">📝 Common PL/SQL questions — quick answers</div>

    <div class="question">What is BULK COLLECT and when do you use it?</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">BULK COLLECT fetches multiple rows into a collection in one go instead of row by row. Use it when processing large datasets to reduce context switches between SQL and PL/SQL engines — significantly improves performance.</div>

    <div class="question" style="margin-top:12px;">Difference between procedure and function?</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">A function must return a value and can be used in SQL queries. A procedure does not have to return a value and is used for performing actions. Functions are used in SELECT statements, procedures are called using EXEC.</div>

    <div class="question" style="margin-top:12px;">What is an Autonomous Transaction?</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">An autonomous transaction runs independently of the parent transaction. Even if the parent rolls back, the autonomous transaction is committed separately. Commonly used for logging errors — you want the log to persist even if the main transaction fails.</div>

    <div class="question" style="margin-top:12px;">How do you tune a slow query?</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">First I run EXPLAIN PLAN or use AWR reports to identify the bottleneck — full table scans, missing indexes, or bad join order. Then I look at DBMS_STATS to check if statistics are stale. I add indexes, rewrite joins, use hints if needed, and verify the improvement with Execution Plan.</div>

    <div class="question" style="margin-top:12px;">What is a REF CURSOR?</div>
    <div class="answer" contenteditable="true">A REF CURSOR is a pointer to a query result set. It allows you to pass query results between programs or return them from stored procedures. Useful for dynamic queries where you don't know the query structure at compile time.</div>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- CHECKLIST TAB -->
<div class="section" id="checklist">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">✅ Before every interview call</div>
    <ul class="checklist" id="check-list">
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Read through the screening script once</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Say the intro out loud at least once</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Check your CTC is filled in above</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Keep resume open on another tab</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Find a quiet place with good signal</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Have a pen and paper ready</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Know the company name and role before the call</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Prepare one question to ask them at the end</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">🏆 Your achievements — drop these naturally</div>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>MVP Award — Infosys H1 2024</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>2nd Place — AI Hackathon Chennai DC</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Infosys RISE Award</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>CMA CGM client appreciation — zero defects</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>Sublease invoice — complex multi-team delivery</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>15+ production releases supported</li>
      <li><div class="check" onclick="toggleCheck(this)"></div>25+ business enhancements delivered</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- RULES TAB -->
<div class="section" id="rules">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">📋 Golden rules for every call</div>
    <div class="rules">
      <div class="rule"><strong>Speak slowly.</strong> Recruiters are taking notes. Pause after key points.</div>
      <div class="rule"><strong>Never badmouth Infosys.</strong> Even if asked why you're leaving. Always frame it positively.</div>
      <div class="rule"><strong>Always say you're interviewing elsewhere.</strong> Creates urgency. Even if you're not.</div>
      <div class="rule"><strong>Give a salary range, never one number.</strong> Always end with "open to discussion."</div>
      <div class="rule"><strong>Ask one question at the end.</strong> Shows genuine interest. Always confirm next steps.</div>
      <div class="rule"><strong>Gap answer — one sentence only.</strong> Don't over-explain. Confidence kills the question.</div>
      <div class="rule"><strong>Keep intro under 45 seconds.</strong> Practice it until it feels natural.</div>
      <div class="rule"><strong>After the call — send a WhatsApp or email.</strong> "Thank you for your time, looking forward to next steps." Most candidates don't do this.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">🚫 Never say these</div>
    <div class="rules">
      <div class="rule" style="border-left-color:#ef4444;"><strong>"My manager is bad"</strong> or anything negative about current team.</div>
      <div class="rule" style="border-left-color:#ef4444;"><strong>"I don't know"</strong> — say "I haven't worked with that directly but I'm familiar with the concept and can pick it up quickly."</div>
      <div class="rule" style="border-left-color:#ef4444;"><strong>"I'll take whatever you offer"</strong> — always give a range.</div>
      <div class="rule" style="border-left-color:#ef4444;"><strong>"I'm not currently interviewing anywhere"</strong> — creates zero urgency.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
function showTab(id) {
  document.querySelectorAll('.section').forEach(s => s.classList.remove('active'));
  document.querySelectorAll('.tab').forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
  document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');
  event.target.classList.add('active');
}

function updateCTC() {
  const val = document.getElementById('ctc-val').value;
  const display = document.getElementById('ctc-display');
  display.textContent = val ? val + ' LPA' : '[fill CTC above]';
}

function toggleCheck(el) {
  el.classList.toggle('done');
}
</script>
</body>
</html>
